 and responded to per sla escalation guidelines rates secure individual & group file storage is available to faculty and staff by subscription and is charged monthly to your department's it services bill see the computing services rates page for more information this service is provided to stanford faculty and staff at the same rate as individual & group file storage getting started your department contact can order secure individual & group file storage for both individual and group accounts via orderit if ordering a group account please provide the name of the stanford workgroup with the orderit after you have placed your order the it services storage group will contact you with details on how to connect to your secure file data storage last modified wed 6 jul 2011 at 17 44 pages about this service overview storage solutions summary chart afs at stanford webafs user guide creating a new folder deleting files and folders downloading files logging in and logging out moving files and folders navigating around webafs renaming files setting favorite locations setting folder permissions uploading files viewing files afs for beginners afs on the desktop navigating afs why afs setting permissions setting permissions with macintosh setting permissions with unix are you allowed to set permissions setting permissions with windows doing more with afs advanced information and commands backups common questions about afs intermediate login problems more about permissions pts groups tokens useful commands system admin information install guide afs supported architectures installing afs on aix 4.3 installing afs on digital unix 4.0 f installing afs on hp ux 11.0 installing afs on irix 6.5 installing afs on red hat linux installing afs on solaris 8 installing afs on solaris 9 afs user guide afs quota automated authentication backups file permissions acls serving web pages from afs tokens your user volume downloadable files stanford afs cell information connection statistics server 